For this specific case, there are a few approaches:

### Approach 1: Define a fully expanded macro before using it

```latex
\def\e1{\tau}
\def\expandedhat{\hat{\e1}}

\begin{tikzpicture}
    \node at (0,0) {$\expandedhat$}; % This will correctly show \hat{\tau}
\end{tikzpicture}
```

### Approach 2: Use `\edef` to force expansion when defining

```latex
\def\e1{\tau}
\edef\e1unit{\noexpand\hat{\e1}}

\begin{tikzpicture}
    \node at (0,0) {$\e1unit$}; % Now shows \hat{\tau}
\end{tikzpicture}
```

### Approach 3: For your specific case

```latex
